snippet.textDisplay:
If you paired Luka with the MVP, gave him a 3-2 lead in the finals, and told him to be extra special for one game, he could do it. While I agree that Magic's game 6 was one of the best ever, Kareem carried that team all year, won the regular season MVP and would have been the Finals MVP if he had not gotten hurt. Through 5 finals games, Kareem was averaging 33.4 pts, 13.6 reb, 3.2 ast, 4.6 blk. He then misses game 6, Magic goes off, and Magic steals Finals MVP. So without trying to take anything away from Magic, Kareem was better in the regular season and better through 5 games of the Finals. But Luka is carrying his team and is an MVP candidate right now, so individually, he is having the best age-20 season of all time and I don't think it's all that close.


Best evidence is MVP voting of age-20 season
Magic - Not in top 9
Lebron - 6
Luka - currently ranked 3rd in race


All these seasons were in different eras, so the best argument is how they performed relative to the rest of the league. If Luka finishes top 5 in MVP voting, he will have the best age 20 season off all time
